title: For Sale:  One-of-a-Kind Kimber Super Match II 1911
postcontent: This one-of-a-kind Kimber Super Match II 1911 pistol, featuring exquisite hand engraving and “SUPER 1911” Serial number is one of two Kimber firearms. This Super Match “SUPER1911” is hand-engraved by Rob Bunting of Baron Engraving in Trumbull, Connecticut. Rob is a highly skilled and creative engraver who has engraved some of the most popular firearms. In explaining the engraving pattern he featured on the Super Match II 1911 (and the SuperAmerica .308 rifle), Rob said, “First off, 1911's are one of my favorites to work on! When I saw the serial number was special, I thought I would try something a little different for this one. I tend to do leafy scroll, which I like very much, but I wanted to simplify the look this time around. This pattern has a very strong central spine with leaves placed more formally at regular intervals. The spine receives very little shading and the leaves are heavily shaded and cross-hatched, which creates a very strong contrast in the design. I think that is what makes it nice. I also removed a fair amount of background from between the scrolls and put in a nice strong punch dot pattern down to increase the contrast. Black fill in the cuts makes the whole thing pull together and pop.” The new Super Match II 1911is designed for competition right out of the box with all new features and an accuracy guarantee of one-inch five-shot groups at 25 yards. The .45 ACP features Kimber adjustable sights, fancy walnut grips and match grade trigger. Barrel length is five inches and weight is 39 ounces with unloaded 8-round magazine.
